text: Alyssa Michelle Stephens (born December 22, 1998), known professionally as Latto (formerly known as Mulatto), is an American rapper and singer- songwriter. She won the first season of the reality television series The Rap Game in 2016 as Miss Mulatto. Her 2019 single "Bitch from da Souf" peaked at number 95 on the Billboard Hot 100 in August 2020. It was accompanied by a remix by rappers Saweetie and Trina. "Muwop" (featuring Gucci Mane) followed. Both songs were certified platinum. They also appeared on Latto's first album Queen of da Souf, which was released in August 2020. The album was re-issued as a deluxe edition in December 2020. Latto's mainstream breakthrough came with the release of "Big Energy", the lead single from her second studio album 777 (2022). It became Latto's highest-charting single to date, peaking at number three on the Billboard Hot 100. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Rappers from Ohio Category:Rappers from Atlanta Category:American pop rappers
